arChildNodes.szComment: Torben hears the player found a dead merchant with their throat torn out. He ponders what coudl do such a thing, and why. (Note: He's intentionally acting like this is new information. Really, this was his hallmark wound as the Bear of Blackweald)
A rowdy drunk believes the wound matches the "Bear of Blackweald," a fabled killer of old. He declares the connection with enthusiasm, drunk mockery.
The local drunk regales the player and Torben with details of the Bear of Blackweald's killing methods and victims. He parades the words with mocking enthusiasm.
Torben coldly dismisses the drunk's claims that the "Bear of Blackweald" has returned, or exists at all.
Torben redirects to focus on the murdered merchant, claiming others have yet to arrive from the east.
Torben voices more concern for the merchants' absense, saying they are not common to be late for drinks. Something is clearly wrong. (Leads player to hunt for missing merchants)
